page.title: 02BEACH LIFE
page.content: Part of the beach in Chapel St.Leonards.The sand is very soft and a golden yellow.On the beach there is a yellow hut it is used for keeping the deckchairs and some of the windbreakers which are made from material.On the beach there are different kinds of shells and stones.In the winter time things get washed up on the beach ,like crabs,starfish and fish.In the summer quite alot of people go on the beach.These are names of shells that you find on the beach,Mussels, Giants toenails.To have a ride on the donkey's it costs fifty pence.There are about ten or eleven donkey's.
